{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS-1 review (criterion T3 — Integration feasibility [overlay]): PASS, no findings.\n\nT3 is an overlay that fires only for EXTERNAL APIs/CLIs/services/libraries or newly-asserted capabilities. This plan's \"integrations\" are all INTERNAL, already-built engine seams — so per the T3 ANTI-FP rule (\"an internal, already-used integration is not-applicable\") the overlay is largely not-applicable. I nonetheless tool-verified each named construct the plan depends on, and every one exists and is operational:\n\n- `batch` step + `BatchRunner` seam + reference `DefaultBatchRunner` — shipped + signed-PASS under epic A (5766, closed): `src/rebar/llm/workflow/runners.py`, `executor.py`.\n- `if:`-overlay precompute pattern (no new IR field) — verified in 5766's `interpreter.py _guard_scoped` + `steps.py` overlay_triggers.\n- Production batch-runner extracted behind the seam — `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/production_batch_runner.py` + `sizing.py` already present.\n- Planned-trace parity harness mechanism — `src/rebar/llm/workflow/trace.py` (`PlannedTraceRunner`, FakeRunner/FakeAgentRunner seam); the plan's load-bearing claim (\"capture the INTENDED model, fake echoes model=None\") matches trace.py L30-31/L45 exactly. A `tests/unit/workflow/test_plan_review_parity.py` and a `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gates/plan-review.yaml` already exist.\n- `execution_mode` call-mode (agent|1-shot) capture — grounded across prompts.py, runner.py, ADR 0001, and trace.py L207-216.\n- Bespoke implementations to migrate — `plan_review/orchestrator.py` and `completion.py` both present.\n\nNo external API/CLI subcommand or endpoint to MATCH against --help/docs; no auth/HTTPS precondition is in play; no critical capability gap routing to a SPIKE. The feasibility is concretely demonstrated by already-closed epic A, so this is a PASS rather than an asserted-but-unverified-capability MAJOR.\n\nAffirmations (T3 checklist):\n- Achievable-as-described: YES — every integration construct exists and is closed/operational.\n- Named subcommands/endpoints exist: N/A (internal seams), and the internal seams named all resolve in code.\n- Auth/HTTPS preconditions: N/A (no external service).\n- Critical-gap→SPIKE: N/A (no capability gap found).\n\n(Non-T3 note for the author, out of this pass's scope: AC5 names `examples/code_review.yaml` + a `templates.py` scaffold as removal targets, but neither file currently exists — `examples/` holds only `review_skeleton.yaml`, and search finds no `templates.py`. The epic's own RE-TRIAGE comment flags the removal set as \"pending Joe's selection.\" Worth reconciling, but that is a G-series/staleness concern, not a T3 integration-feasibility finding.)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782507439299055001,"uuid":"723ef2eb-8cc7-4a4f-9025-49215efd3d32"}